  "text": "Firefox Content Security Policy Enforcement Infrastructure Audit\n\n1. **CSP Directive Parser (nsCSPParser)**\n   - Location: dom/security/nsCSPParser.h (definition at line 41)\n   - Implementation: dom/security/nsCSPParser.cpp\n   - Primary class: nsCSPParser\n   - Key method: static nsCSPPolicy* parseContentSecurityPolicy()\n   - Purpose: Parses CSP policy strings into policy objects using a finite state machine parser following the W3C CSP source-list grammar\n   - Functionality: Tokenizes input, validates directives, and builds nsCSPPolicy objects\n\n2. **CSP Context Management (nsCSPContext)**\n   - Location: dom/security/nsCSPContext.h (definition at line 40)\n   - Implementation: dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp\n   - Primary class: nsCSPContext\n   - XPCOM Details: Implements nsIContentSecurityPolicy interface (contract ID: @mozilla.org/cspcontext;1)\n   - Contract ID: NS_CSPCONTEXT_CONTRACTID (@mozilla.org/cspcontext;1)\n   - GUID: 09d9ed1a-e5d4-4004-bfe0-27ceb923d9ac\n   - Key responsibilities: Holds multiple CSP policies, evaluates policy compliance, manages violation reporting\n\n3. **CSP Violation Reporting**\n   - Location: dom/security/nsCSPContext.cpp (violation reporting at lines 776, 822)\n   - Primary method: LogViolationDetails() (line 776)\n   - Supporting method: LogViolationDetailsUnchecked() (line 822)\n   - Supporting utilities: nsCSPUtils.h and nsCSPUtils.cpp\n   - Utility location: dom/security/nsCSPUtils.h and dom/security/nsCSPUtils.cpp\n   - Reporting types: Supports violation type constants for inline scripts, eval, styles, nonces, hashes, and trusted-types violations\n   - CSPViolationData handling: Constructs SecurityPolicyViolationEventInit structures, sends reports to endpoints or report-uri\n\n4. **XPCOM Interface Declaration**\n   - Location: dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl\n   - Interface: nsIContentSecurityPolicy\n   - UUID: 1d632008-6c97-48ae-a51c-16e2daa0f4f6\n   - CSPDirective enum defined at line 47, includes:\n     * SCRIPT_SRC_DIRECTIVE (line 50) - main script-src directive\n     * SCRIPT_SRC_ELEM_DIRECTIVE (line 69) - script-src-elem for inline script elements\n     * SCRIPT_SRC_ATTR_DIRECTIVE (line 70) - script-src-attr for event handler attributes\n     * And 24 other directives total (NO_DIRECTIVE through REPORT_TO_DIRECTIVE)\n   - Key methods declared: getAllowsInline(), getAllowsEval(), logViolationDetails()\n\n5. **Inline Script-src Evaluation**\n   - Location: dom/script/ScriptLoader.cpp (inline check at lines 1056-1062)\n   - Method: Inline script evaluation check for CSP compliance\n   - Mechanism: Calls GetAllowsInline() on nsCSPContext with SCRIPT_SRC_ELEM_DIRECTIVE\n   - Parameters: directive type, unsafe hash flag, nonce, parser created flag, element, source text, line/column numbers\n   - Return value: Boolean indicating whether inline script is allowed by CSP\n   - Usage context: Called during script element processing to determine if inline script content should execute\n   - Directive used: nsIContentSecurityPolicy::SCRIPT_SRC_ELEM_DIRECTIVE\n\nAll files are located under dom/security/ except ScriptLoader.cpp (dom/script/) and the XPCOM interface (dom/interfaces/security/)."
}

